Product Name: Aptamil Gold Follow up Infant Formula Powder - With Prebiotics, DHA, Iron, After 12 Months, Stage 3, 400 g Bag-In-Box
Product Description: Aptamil Stage 3 Follow up formula contains balanced, age-appropriate nutrients which support the overall growth and development of the baby. Formulated with the optimized blend of DHA & ARA to support brain development and visual acuity. Boil drinking water for 5 minutes and leave it till lukewarm 
Pour the correct amount of lukewarm water as per the feeding table
Consult feeding table and add into the bowl of exact number of scoops, levelled off according to the age of the infant. Use only the scoop provided with the pack. Stir well till the powder dissolves.

Care Instruction:
Storage Instructions: On opening this pack, the contents along with the laminate pouch should immediately be transferred to an empty, clean, dry and airtight container. Replace the lid tightly after each use and store in a cool dry place. After opening, use the contents within 3 weeks or the expiry date whichever is earlier. The scoop and water measuring cup provided with the cap should be thoroughly washed and dried before use.

Warning: Careful and hygienic preparation of infant milk substitutes is essential for health. Do not use fewer scoops than directed, since diluted feeding will not provide adequate nutrients needed by your infant. Do not use more scoops than directed, since concentrated feed will not provide the water needed by your infant. Infant milk substitutes are only on the advice of a health worker as to the need for its use and the proper method of its use. Infant milk substitute or infant food is not the sole source of nourishment for an infant. It is important to follow the mentioned feeding and storage instructions while using the infant formula for your baby's well-being.
Caution: Unboiled water, unsterilized bowls/spoons or incorrect dilution may endanger the infants health. Prepare only one feed at a time. Use prepared feed immediately (within half an hour), otherwise, microbial deterioration may set in. Discard unused feed. Always hold the baby while feeding. Leaving the baby unattended may cause choking.

Usage:
Wash your hands before preparing the babys food. Make sure all utensils are thoroughly clean.
Boil clean drinking water for 5 minutes. Allow cooling. Measure 75ml and pour lukewarm water into babys bowl.
Add 3 levelled scoops of Cerelac.
Stir until the cereal is smooth and feed immediately using a clean spoon.
Optimal Preparation: Careful and hygienic preparation of Infant food is most essential for health. Do not use fewer scoops than directed, since diluted feeding will not provide adequate nutrients needed by your infant. Do not use more scoops than directed since concentrated feed will not provide the water needed by your infant.
Storage: After opening the pack, the contents should immediately be transferred to an empty, clean, dry and airtight container. Replace the lid tightly after every use and store it in a cool, dry place. Ensure the enclosed scoop is thoroughly washed and dried before use. After opening, use the contents within 3 weeks or the expiry date, whichever is earlier.
Important Notice: Mothers milk is best for your baby.
Safety Warnings: Infant food should be used only on the advice of a health worker as to the need for its use and the proper method of its use. Infant food is not the sole source of nourishment for an infant. Use prepared feed within half an hour otherwise microbial deterioration may set in. Discard unused feed.

Product Name: Timios Porridge - Organic Millet Khichdi, For Babies 10+ Months, 200 g
Product Description:
1) Made using cleanroom technology
2) Made to Order for maximum freshness
Manufacturer: Firm roots Pvt Ltd, D-14/A, TSIIC INDUSTRIAL PARK, Lalapet - Moula Ali Road, Musi Nagar, Moula Ali, Secunderabad, Telangana 500040
Usage:
Take 2 levelled scoops of the porridge powder in a vessel
Add 100 ml water and mix well
Cook on a medium flame for 2-3 mins while stirring continuously to avoid lumps
Check for the desired temperature of the prepared porridge by tasting it yourself before feeding it to the baby
Start with one scoop initially * You can increase the amount according to the babys intake
